# Initialize Phoenix project

Create the base Phoenix application structure without HTML/assets (API-only).

## Requirements

- [ ] Run `mix phx.new pag_server --no-html --no-assets --database postgres`
- [ ] Verify directory structure matches plan
- [ ] Run `mix deps.get` to fetch dependencies
- [ ] Run `mix compile` to verify compilation
- [ ] Create initial git commit with message "Initial Phoenix project setup"

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `mix compile` passes with zero warnings
- [ ] `mix test` runs successfully (even with no tests yet)
- [ ] Directory structure includes:
  - [ ] `lib/pag_server/` (core business logic)
  - [ ] `lib/pag_server_web/` (web layer)
  - [ ] `test/` (mirrors lib structure)
  - [ ] `config/` (runtime config files)
  - [ ] `priv/repo/migrations/` (database migrations)
- [ ] Git repository initialized with .gitignore
- [ ] No compilation errors or warnings
- [ ] Default Phoenix tests pass

## Context

**Plan References**:
- `.plan/2026-02-05-velvet-cascade/index.md` Section 1.2 (OTP Application Structure)
- `.plan/2026-02-05-velvet-cascade/architecture.md` Section 2.1 (Top-Level Organization)

**Key Points**:
- Use PostgreSQL as default database (production target)
- API-only: `--no-html --no-assets` creates Phoenix Channels + REST API project
- This forms the foundation for all subsequent work

## Notes

The `mix phx.new` command creates:
```
pag_server/
├── lib/
│   ├── pag_server/         # Business logic goes here
│   │   ├── application.ex  # OTP application supervisor
│   │   └── repo.ex         # Database repository
│   ├── pag_server_web/     # Web layer goes here
│   │   ├── endpoint.ex     # HTTP/WebSocket endpoint
│   │   └── router.ex       # Route definitions
│   └── pag_server.ex       # Root module
├── test/                   # Test files mirror lib/
├── config/                 # Configuration files
├── priv/repo/migrations/   # Database migrations
└── mix.exs                 # Project definition
```

Take time to verify the structure is correct before committing.
